snippet.textDisplay:
I was in North Carolina once and happened upon a Gem store where you could mine your own rocks out of some blown up gravel from the ground and I remember the guide telling me how much the gems we found were worth so much and would be worth so much more if we paid him to tumble and restore the gems for us.

Bottom line: I believe it's all just a scam. Not all a scam, but for the most part, they over estimate what it's worth. It's not worth that much until the shape and colors are restored into a perfect condition.
snippet.textOriginal:

Bottom line: I believe it's all just a scam. Not all a scam, but for the most part, they over estimate what it's worth. It's not worth that much until the shape and colors are restored into a perfect condition.
